<seg id="750">& dot; algorithm, the standard for directional graphs. it produces hierarchical or layered representations of directional graphs. the algorithm gives the edges in the same direction (from top to bottom or from left to right) and then tries to produce as short edges as possible and as few edges of edges as possible.</seg>
<seg id="751">Der & neato; algorithm is the standard for ungerized graphs. it produces presentations in accordance with the bounce spring model. the Kamada Kawai algorithm is used, which is synonymous with statistical multidimensional scaling.</seg>
<seg id="752">The & fdp; algorithm creates a spring- spring model for unerified graphs. it uses the Fruchterman-Reingold heuristic, and includes a multi-grid trigger for the treatment of large and clustered graphs.</seg>
